June 1, 2024
 I am currently developing an application for my business. The purpose of the application is to calculate billing for my business's customers. The front end will be a JavaScript and React app, and the back end will use Flask with Python. The database will be PostgreSQL. I need to create the schema for the application. There will be a lot of extremely complex calculations for invoicing customers, which will require intricate business logic, special rules, special pricing rules, and dealing with different pricing models.

To develop a robust billing application with PostgreSQL as the database, let's outline the high-level steps and then proceed to define the schema. The application will manage customers, products, invoices, and billing rules.

