When you query the products_partitioned table, PostgreSQL can skip partitions that don’t match the query criteria, reducing the amount of data scanned and improving performance.
Summary
Partitioning is a powerful technique to manage large tables by dividing them into smaller, more manageable pieces. It improves query performance, eases maintenance, enhances bulk operations, and ensures better data locality. By carefully choosing the partitioning strategy, you can significantly optimize your database performance and manageability.

