Services Table:

Stores details about the services offered, including name, description, and pricing.
Automatically updates updated_at timestamp when records are updated.
Service Logs Table:

Logs each instance of a service performed, including references to the customer and SKU.
Calculates and stores the total cost based on the quantity and unit price of the service.
Ensures referential integrity with customers and products tables.
Automatically updates updated_at timestamp when records are updated.
